## 2. Functional Requirements

<!-- Source: Phase 0 Step 0.1. See builders-guide.md for the full prompt and review checklist. -->

### Must-Have (MVP)

[Features that ship first. For each requirement, use the format:
- **[Feature Name]:** If [condition], the system must [action] and output [result]. Failure state: [what happens when this fails — error message, fallback behavior, or explicit non-recovery].]

### Should-Have (v1.1)

[Features targeted for the release immediately after MVP. These are planned but not committed. Each item should be specific enough to scope — not "better UX" but "users can reset their password without contacting support."]

### Will-Not-Have

[Explicit scope boundaries for this release. At least 3 items. If something is commonly assumed to be included in a product like this, list it here to prevent scope creep. Format: "**[Feature]:** [Why it is excluded or deferred]." ]

