## 4. Data Contracts

<!-- Source: Phase 0 Step 0.3. See builders-guide.md for the full prompt and review checklist. -->

### Inputs

[For each input the system accepts: **[Input name]:** Type: [data type]. Validation rules: [constraints, format, range]. Sensitivity: [Public / Internal / Confidential / Restricted].]

### Transformations

[Each processing step the system performs on data, expressed as a discrete operation. Format: **[Step N]:** [Input] → [Operation] → [Output]. No black boxes — if you cannot describe the transformation, it is not ready to build.]

### Outputs

[For each output the system produces: **[Output name]:** Format: [file type, API response shape, display format]. Latency expectation: [acceptable wait time from user perspective].]

### Third-Party Data

[For each external API or data source: **[Source name]:** Used for: [purpose]. Fallback if unavailable: [degraded behavior or error handling]. Caching: [TTL or none].]

### State

[What persists across sessions vs. what is ephemeral. Format: **[Data element]:** Persists / Ephemeral. If persists: [where stored, retention period].]

