## Appendix A: Revenue Model & Unit Economics

<!-- Standard+ Track only. Skip for internal tools. Source: Step 0.5. See builders-guide.md for the full prompt and review checklist. -->

**Pricing Model:** [Free / Freemium / Subscription / One-time purchase / Usage-based / Enterprise license. Describe the model briefly.]

**Per-User Costs:** [Estimated infrastructure, API, and support cost per active user per month. Show your math.]

**Break-Even User Count:** [Number of paying users required to cover ongoing operating costs at the chosen price point.]

**Hosting Cost Ceiling:**
- At 1,000 users: $[X]/month
- At 10,000 users: $[X]/month

[If either number is unacceptable, the pricing model or architecture must change before Phase 1. Do not proceed with an architecture that produces unsustainable unit economics.]

