Self-assessment of your ability to validate AI-generated output in each domain. Honest assessment here determines where human review is the control vs. where an automated tool is needed.

| Domain | Can I Validate? | If No: Automated Tool |
|---|---|---|
| Product / UX Logic | Yes / No | — |
| Frontend / UI | Yes / No | [Tool, e.g., Storybook, Playwright visual] |
| Backend / API | Yes / No | [Tool, e.g., contract tests, Postman] |
| Database | Yes / No | [Tool, e.g., migration dry-run, schema diff] |
| Security | Yes / No | [Tool, e.g., Semgrep, gitleaks, Snyk] |
| Build & Packaging | Yes / No | [Tool, e.g., CI pipeline, release smoke test] |
| Accessibility | Yes / No | [Tool, e.g., axe-core, NVDA, VoiceOver] |
| Performance | Yes / No | [Tool, e.g., Lighthouse, k6, Instruments] |
| Platform-Specific | Yes / No | [Tool specific to web / desktop / mobile] |

[For any domain where you answered No and have no automated tool: either acquire the tooling before Phase 2 or explicitly accept the risk and record it here as a known gap.]

